<h2>What Are Surplus Funds & Excess Proceeds?</h2>

<p>
When a foreclosure sale or tax auction generates more money than what was owed, the leftover amount is called surplus funds, excess proceeds, or overages. These excess proceeds occur when the final auction price exceeds the mortgage debt, taxes, liens, and foreclosure costs owed on the property. :contentReference[oaicite:7]{index=7}
</p>

<p>
Surplus funds may legally belong to the former homeowner or their heirs, but they are <strong>not automatically paid</strong> out — a formal claim must be filed with the appropriate authority to recover the funds. :contentReference[oaicite:8]{index=8}
</p>

<p>
